Description: Fragment of oval handle at neck join to sharpish turn from a possibly Koan pottery transport amphora. Clay medium, micaceous, red-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Perhaps to be equated with Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47) 121,11.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0220)
